To plot indicator values, in the OnData event handler, call the Plot method.

private SuperTrend _str;

// In Initialize()
var symbol = AddEquity("SPY").Symbol;
_str = STR(symbol, period, multiplier);

// In OnData()
if (_str.IsReady)
{
    Plot("My Indicators", "basicupperband", _str.BasicUpperBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "basiclowerband", _str.BasicLowerBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "currenttrailingupperband", _str.CurrentTrailingUpperBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "currenttrailinglowerband", _str.CurrentTrailingLowerBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "supertrend", _str.Current.Value);
}
# In Initialize()
symbol = self.AddEquity("SPY").Symbol
self.str = self.STR(symbol, period, multiplier)

# In OnData()
if self.str.IsReady:
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "basicupperband", self.str.BasicUpperBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "basiclowerband", self.str.BasicLowerBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "currenttrailingupperband", self.str.CurrentTrailingUpperBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "currenttrailinglowerband", self.str.CurrentTrailingLowerBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "supertrend", self.str.Current.Value)
